 ago · featured in forbes and inc · upvoted by saravanan ganesh software engineer at google present and jesse collins former software engineer intern at yelp i think at this point everyone can agree that google search and it’s associated adwords business is a monopoly in every sense of the word on the web they’re probably well over  of the market and on mobile it’s nearly  while operating a monopoly is not illegal it does mean your operations and conduct are subject to additional rules regulations and scrutiny primarily to ensure you’re not maintaining that monopoly illegally from my perspective there is no question that google is both harming consumers and illegally defending their monopoly by restricting distribution of key comp more in what areas does yelp have the most room for growth   jeremy stoppelman ceo and cofounder of yelpanswered w ago · featured in huffpost · upvoted by laurence wilson general counsel at yelpconsumer adoption and advertiser growth remain low hanging fruit while most of us here know yelp and well yelp only has unaided brand awareness of about  among digital adults in the us similarly we only have about a third penetration among smartphone users and we have about  million monthly users of our mobile app that is a lot of opportunity to make more consumers aware of yelp and get them using the yelp appon the local business front there are about  million local businesses in the us and about  million in the countries where yelp exists only  businesses currentl more how would you compare yelps product development team to others google facebook etc   jeremy stoppelman ceo and cofounder of yelpanswered w ago · upvoted by jesse collins and kelvin ho former product manager at google in a recent internal engagement survey  of our employees said yelp was a great place to work im really proud of the culture weve built and imho its a very special place almost all of our managers and leadership team has been home grown and we pride ourselves on developing our own talent whenever possible our engineering internship program has been a huge success through the years and i think our oncampus reputation at top universities backs that up generally product and engineering folks would have wider ranging responsibilities than at other major tech brands for example whe more given the seemingly arbitrary yelp sorted reviews how can they prove that yelp doesnt rate paid advertisers preferentially   jeremy stoppelman ceo and cofounder of yelpanswered w ago · featured in huffpost · upvoted by laurence wilson works at yelpevery day our automated software goes through the more than  million reviews that have been submitted to yelp to select the most useful and reliable content unlike many other sites our stance is quality over quantity when it comes to reviews as a result we only recommend about  of the reviews that are submitted if advertisers could control their reviews then you’d expect them all to have perfect star ratings on yelp spoiler alert they don’t to test this do a few searches in broad categories in your area  maybe for a dentist mattress or locksmith you’ll find ads for busi more has any rogue yelp salesman ever been caught extorting a small business   jeremy stoppelman ceo and cofounder of yelpanswered w ago · upvoted by luther lowe works at yelp and andrew martinezfonts works at yelpno we’ve never caught a sales rep threatening to lower a business’s rating if the business didn’t buy advertising that may surprise conspiracy theorists who love the yelp extortion meme but it doesn’t really surprise us we have a range of controls in place to prevent this sort of thing and my best guess is that we are far ahead of anyone else in the industry on this issue precisely because we’ve been in the spotlight for so long  many of our controls are obvious like making sure that sales reps don’t have administrative access to post and remove reviews  others are a little less obv more whats the solution to san franciscos housing shortage   jeremy stoppelman ceo and cofounder of yelpanswered w ago · upvoted by andy anderson lives in san francisco ca and jay wacker lived in the bay area since build baby build nimbys have dominated the development conversation in major cities across the nation this problem is particularly acute in san francisco where economic and population growth have been robust but building hasnt remotely kept up while antidevelopment groups and voices often older and wealthier have long been heard both at various city meetings and through voting young people often dont vote and arent particularly well organized this ultimately means their views arent fairly represented which is why ive financially backed sfbarf a prorenters group that advocate more are restaurants afraid to be unique and take risks because theyre slaves to yelp reviews   jeremy stoppelman ceo and cofounder of yelpanswered w agonate silver did a study comparing yelp restaurant ratings to michelin which relies on professional critics and found them to be quite similar while yelp represents a new way to get reliable recommendations on restaurants and other businesses the idea of publicly critiquing is nothing new and yelp is unlikely to have had a negative impact on the creativity of chefs and food entrepreneurs if anything it gives a new and powerful way for nontraditional food providers like food trucks to market themselves since yelp isnt limited to the high endk views ·  upvoteswhat do you think of google my business listings and reviews   jeremy stoppelman ceo and cofounder of yelpanswered w agoi think its a weak product that generally does consumers a disservice there are much more trusted and reliable ratingsreview resources available across the web and mobile and its a real shame that those options are buried under inferior houseowned google results perhaps its easiest to show by example lets take a popular newish restaurant in san francisco liholiho yacht club yelp has  detailed reviews our ratings have meaty text explaining whats behind the stars and over  photos of the food drinks and business google locals page has  reviews and  of these have more what is yelps strategy for addressing businesses that offer incentives for positive reviews   jeremy stoppelman ceo and cofounder of yelpanswered w agowe have a number of ways of attacking this the first line of defense is our recommendation algorithm it can spot unusual activity and reviews are automatically moved to the not recommended section off the page obviously if youre a business owner providing a valuable incentive for a positive review and those reviews dont stick to your business page you wont be happy with the outcome and most likely will stop doing it we also run sting operations and will post evidence and a prominent consumer alert on the business pagek views ·  upvoteshow can yelp positively affect small business and help them grow   jeremy stoppelman ceo and cofounder of yelpanswered w ago · featured in huffpostyelp levels the playing field between small local businesses and mass chains allowing them to earn new customers based purely on doing an incredible job day in and out vs simply having a massive advertising budget thanks to yelp amazing local businesses now get free exposure just for having a great product and delivering good service we know that  of yelp users spend money at a local business within a week after searching on yelp that kind of purchase intent drives dollars directly to small businesses and if they use the free tools we give them like responding to reviews business more moremoreshare sessiontwitterfacebookk followersshow all people asked aboutvaluations and other market myths i’ve been an angel investor for many years and have seen a lot of ups and downswhat it’s like to work at yelp i get this question a lot and it’s a great opportunity to talk about our unique culture and what we’ve done to protect that culture from startup mode to a  person companywhat’s happening to the first amendment we’re focused on ensuring consumers have online protections for their freedom of speech many small businesses don’t like yelp because they would prefer to keep their unhappy customers quiet but the first amendment matters and we’re not backing down does yelp extort small businesses no and there’s no amount of money you can pay yelp to manipulate a business rating let’s set the record straightrockstar in your late s that’d be nice started learning guitar  years ago and i’m pretty hooked let’s talk about picking up something new and challenging in your adult life and why i’m not leaving my day job to hit the road anytime soonyelp policies and our review algorithm designed from day  to protect our users and community by ensuring that the content we trust most is what’s informing the spending decisions of millions of consumers around the globewhat’s our beef with google and why it’s important  however unpopular  that we challenge the influence and power of one of the world’s most loved brands the role business leaders and businesses can play in solving social issues from preventing legalized discrimination to promoting fair and affordable housing and countless other challenges communities are facing big businesses and their employees can play a key role in driving changeupcoming sessionsview all jeannette walls author of the glass castleanswering sat at  am pdt betty liu founderceo of radiatetaking questions on insert a dynamic date heresitemapabcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyzabout · careers · privacy · terms · contact jeremy stoppelman on twitter for those questioning apples continued product chopsinnovation check out airpods a product that i think would make steve proud skip to content home home home current page moments moments moments current page search query search twitter saved searches remove in this conversation verified accountprotected tweets  suggested users verified accountprotected tweets  verified accountprotected tweets  language english bahasa indone