 to know to start doing accountbased marketingcreate your first accountbased marketing campaign using this simple stepbystep guide download nowread more at metadataioanswer wiki answer george weisgerber iii has advised small business owners  entrepreneurs as well as fortune  ceosanswered w agoyelp provides an abundance of support to help small businesses engage with new and existing customers on their platform such as a dashboard filled with analytics online ordering with no setup fee a great mobile app and more if your business has a poor yelp rating because of a few biased reviews here are three steps you can take to improve itaddress the “heavily biased” reviews below are my recommendations for addressing negative reviews depending on the reason you feel they’re “heavily biased”the review is fake not only is the author not a customer you believe they are a competitor disgruntled employee etcrespond to the review publicly with proof that the review is fake your reply should be professional  matteroffact take the highroad and don’t write anything that reflects negatively on you or your business remember you’re composing this response to inform your customers not to insult your competition or former employeeflag the review by logging into either the yelp for business owners mobile app or website and clicking “report this review” provide as much relevant and factual information for the moderator that will be evaluating the validity of your claim follow up with an email to feedbackyelpcomthe review is from an actual customer although you feel the review is totally biased and nottrue it was written by a one of your leads or customerssend a private message to the customer who left the review respond diplomatically and thank the reviewer for their feedback perhaps this is a simple misunderstanding that can be rectified and possibly lead to the customer leaving an updated reviewif that doesn’t work respond publicly potential customers will get to read your side of the story and see that your business is responsive to feedbackproactively create opportunities for positive reviews now that you’ve addressed the bad you can start focusing on the good place a find us on yelp sign near the cash wrap or a sticker in your windowupdate your email signature by adding a yelp icon with a link to your page followed by “the best compliment is a star review”if you see a customer checkin on yelp twitter foursquare or any other platform leave a comment thanking them for stopping by and let them know you appreciate any feedback they can provide followed by a link to your yelp page keep em’ coming back for more a harvard study found that a onestar increase in a business’s yelp rating leads to – more revenue so don’t stop just because you’ve gotten a few good reviews to balance out those “heavily biased” ones be sure to respond to all new reviews asap and follow these three quick steps to attract new customers to your business via yelpmake sure you business’s address hours phone  and website info are updatedupload enticing images and videos of your businessyelp allows your business to be listed in up to three categories take advantage of all three for instance if you have a pizzeria that serves other dishes and offers catering be sure you’re listed under italian food and catering not just pizzai understand how frustrating it can be to read negative things about your business especially heavily biased reviews you didn’t invest your blood sweat tears and treasure into your small business so some knucklehead could go disparage you online remember why you did though to build something that’s yours to do what you love and to serve those customers who love your food service clothing etcgeorge weisgerber iii wwwlocalangelnyc viewspromoted by toptalgreat developers and designers are hard to findlet toptal match you with the top  of developers and designers for your next project norisk trialsign up at toptalcomview more answersrelated questionsjeremy stoppelman 